ATP} ={2NH}_{3}+{\rm{H}}_{2}+ {16ADP} + {16 Pi}.$$
\end{document}

Denitrification is the conversion of nitrate to gaseous compounds (nitric oxide, nitrous oxide, and N2) by microorganisms. Denitrification goes through some combination of the following intermediate forms:
